<DocLayout title="Tasks" description="Task management, Kanban boards, and task dependencies in Yet.Project.">
  <h1>Tasks</h1>

  <p>
    Tasks are the core work items in Yet.Project. This guide covers creating, managing, and organizing tasks.
  </p>

  <h2>Creating Tasks</h2>

  <h3>From the Web App</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Open a project</li>
    <li>Click <strong>"New Task"</strong> or press <code>C</code></li>
    <li>Enter the task title</li>
    <li>Add optional details (description, priority, assignee)</li>
    <li>Press <code>Enter</code> or click <strong>"Create"</strong></li>
  </ol>

  <h3>From Claude/AI</h3>
  <p>Just ask your AI assistant:</p>
  <pre><code>"Create a task to implement user authentication in the MYAPP project"</code></pre>

  <h3>From CLI</h3>
  <pre><code>{`yet task create "Implement user authentication" \\
  --project MYAPP \\
  --priority high \\
  --label feature`}</code></pre>

  <h2>Task Fields</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Field</th>
